Thirty four ships laden with petroleum products, food items and other goods are expected to arrive Apapa and Tin Can Island Ports in Lagos between Monday and April 27. The Nigerian Ports Authority ( NPA ) stated this in its publication, ‘Shipping Position’, a copy of which was made available to our correspondent in Lagos on Monday. 15 of the expected 34 ships would sail in with petrol. NPA said that the remaining 19 ships contained bulk wheat,  bulk sugar, bulk frozen fish, ethanol, bulk fertiliser, general cargo and containers laden with goods. The document indicated that 10 ships had arrived the ports  and waiting to berth with bulk fertiliser and petrol. NAN